column5: Great day today, missed a biggun, upper 40's with awesome girth and then netted this fine 46.25 x 18.5! Another boat out with us had a double header 42" and 46". Very productive day but exhausted now lol. Going to repeat tomorrow!
Good start to your season Matt.
Friends Steve Tony from New Brunswick with a double header! Awesome Awesome day, with a few more caught as well. The Ottawa is a gem!
Nice going Matt. With any luck I will be there June 29. Glad to see the NB guys getting fish!
Nice fish, I hope to get out here tomorrow!
Very nice start Matt congrats to the boys from the east.
Hope those fish are back on the feed again in about 9 days from now Matt. See you then.
Great skis!  I wish my stretch of the ott had a good population of them (too far north i guess)
.25...? Who measures to a 1/4"???   REALLY MATT?
.25...? Who measures to a 1/4"???   REALLY MATT? YUP  Nice smile in the bass pics Dax!
